Caring for your eyebrows is an important part of your beauty routine. Not only do eyebrows help frame your face, but they also play an essential role in your overall facial expression. Here are some tips on how to care for your eyebrows: Regular trimming: Use a spoolie brush to comb your eyebrow hairs upward, then trim any stray hairs that extend beyond the natural shape of your brows. Shaping: If you need to reshape your brows, use a pencil to outline the desired shape, then pluck or wax any hairs that fall outside of the lines. Moisturizing: Apply a nourishing eyebrow oil or balm to keep your eyebrow hairs healthy and
hydrated. Avoid over-tweezing: Over-tweezing can cause permanent damage to your eyebrow hair follicles, so itâ€™s important to only pluck or wax hairs that fall outside of your natural brow shape. Types of eyebrows and their features: Straight eyebrows: Straight eyebrows have little to no arch and create a more neutral expression. Arched eyebrows: Arched eyebrows have a prominent arch and can create a more dramatic
expression. Rounded eyebrows: Rounded eyebrows have a slight curve and can create a softer, more
natural expression. S-shaped eyebrows: S-shaped eyebrows have two arches, creating a more complex
expression.
